texts.text: >After seeing the people of the angry mob off to the hospital or the police department,
>you and Jeng Yun return to Akihabara and the hideout.
We're back.
You did good out there.
Thanks.
Same to you, [sys user_name]. But what the heck...
What's this "Amour" business about anyway?
Oh, you know something about Amour, Jeng Yun?
Hey, you've heard of Amour too?
Yes, she's been all the talk on social media for a while now.
Her posts get hundreds and thousands of replies because of her popularity,
but she actually reads and answers all of them without using a template, which fuels her popularity even more...
Even so, that kind of thing isn't unheard of amongst influencers,
but now people are starting riots around town shouting her name.
Do they say something like "Amour's mine!"?
Yes, yes! That's it!
They will shout her name over and over again,  like zealots in a trance.
And to tell the truth, there's something dodgy about her.
Dodgy?
Yeah, she rouses up people's desires for no reason...
And the name... It's the French word for love right?
Isn't that a bit too obvious? Love and Desire?
Do you guys know that the black lily is the flower that symbolizes love?
Huh?
All flowers have a meaning in Japanese tradition, don't you know that?
I'm no expert, but yes I know that.
But I thought there are other flowers that symbolize love as well.
Nay my good sir, you are mistaken.
The black lily is the only flower to stand for the purely romantic type of love.
I know because I did a lot of research on the subject
when I was writing my piece for the light novel contest.
Hmm, I see... The black lily... Hey, you're right.
See?
>You repeat the words "Black Lily" inside your mind.
(Black Lily... Black Lily...)
Whoa! Newbie, where are you going?!
>Reminded of something,
>you leave the room in a hurry.
Hi Amour.
It's you, isn't it?

*Chuckle*
Very straightforward.
I kinda like that. It shows your passionate side.
What's me?
I'm afraid I won't be able to understand you unless you speak more clearly, darlin'.
...Just kidding.
You're right. I am Amour.
You look surprised. You were expecting me to deny your accusation?
But I haven't done anything wrong though, have I?
All I did was give them a slight jolt, enough to make those with suppressed desires open up to their feelings.
Like the man you saved for instance...
If left in the state you found him in, his life would've been meaningless.
He might've even ended it himself.
>You think back on the state that the man was in when you saved him.
But I'm like a zombie anyway.
Wouldn't have made much difference if I actually died.
You see my point?
You hurt those people.
It's wrong.
They wanted too much too fast.
They weren't able to control their impulses, letting their emotions get the better of them.
But that's not unusual among you humans, right?
The world will always punish those who get too greedy.
Take a look.
>Lilith holds up Arisa's smartphone for you to see.
>The top article on the news site reads...
>"Famous actor wounded in stabbing. Relationship gone bad?"
>in bold letters.
This incident had nothing to do with my influence, but it still happened.
Besides, my influence wasn't all bad. Good things happened too, right?
>You think back on how a lot of people's lives became more joyful.
Hehe, it's kinda embarrassing, but I'm trying to impress a girl...
I assume she's a girl, but it doesn't really matter which sex she is.
I think Jeng's body is attractive, and I'm a guy!
I can tell by your face that you realize I have a point.
I have the ability to add just one drop of desire to the vessel that is Man.
I can erase the notion that wanting something is bad.
So open up your heart, darlin'.
Follow your desires.
>Lilith holds out her hand to you.
>You again think back on all the people you met.
I mean, people these days are so sensitive about that kind of thing. If you show your desire, they'll crucify you.
I guess my desire to become the kind of man that she likes won out.
And now I feel so alive!
>You think back on how that man beamed in happiness.
>Maybe people will make faces like that more, if only they could be a little more open to their own desires.
>But...
It's still too much.
Humans are not like demons.
So you're saying humans and demons have different capacities for desire?
>You nod your head and say:
>A small drop of desire to you is still too much for us. It will overflow our vessel and drown us.
So, I'm sorry. But no.
In time, maybe.

*Chuckle*
You're giving me the cold shoulder.
In that case, you're no use to me. I'm going home.
>Lilith turns her back to you and takes one step forward.
A parting word of advice to reward you for taking the time to reach a proper decision.
Be careful how you handle desire.
When it comes floating to the surface from the darkest depths of your soul, deal with it wisely.
For you have the potential to
change the world with a tap of your finger.
...I am telling you this because we demons have no wish for humanity to end either.
>With that, Lilith steps into the Summoning Portal and disappears...
>After Lilith left,
>you lost your ability to sense "Desire Medals".
>But...
If you had the power to shape the world to your liking,
what kind of world would you build?
For you have the potential to
change the world with a tap of your finger.
>You can't seem to get Lilith's words off of your mind...
They're so cute when they're troubled. Be troubled. Be contemplative.
Because that's the only way to find your true desire. That one thing that makes life worthwhile.
Overflowing desire is what makes humans shine and feel alive...
But your light shines differently than others.
It is small, but it's strong... I can feel it even as it slumbers.
I pray that one day it may become a powerful weapon for you.
A weapon to point at God,
who saw desire as sin and made the world a dull place.
